<task id="task_E5E388513F574717968511936B502205">
  <title>Create a card</title>
  <shortdesc>Create a card in the Marketing Cloud and create a card from a
	 file. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Marketing Cloud" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <steps id="steps_6F909608E436409AB704C13B8698A3B6">
      <step id="step_35DF37D9C8DD4C288897B48996828E0D">
        <cmd>
          <xref href="t_sign_in.xml#task_1BFE87E20DCB44078CAC82F3CD44B985" format="dita" scope="local">
            <?xm-replace_text Sign in to the Adobe Marketing Cloud?>
          </xref> or into a solution. 
		  </cmd>
      </step>
      <step id="step_408E5345E17544928271C9F15988548B">
        <cmd>
          <xref href="t_create_board.xml#task_CF611F6613734EFB9365F6C71520F928" format="dita" scope="local">
            <?xm-replace_text Create a board?>
          </xref>. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <?xm-replace_text Step Result?>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_B50AF131AE5B47CEB56E5B98270A8DD3">
        <cmd>To create a card from a file, open the board, then click 
			 <uicontrol>Create Card from File</uicontrol>. (<image href="graphics/card_from_file_icon.png" id="image_978792EAE3F54710B3A898EE66B053DA"></image>) 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <p>Browse to locate the file. 
			 </p>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
      <step id="step_F633A6DE66D54617B42E9FF79ABE6F8F">
        <cmd>Alternatively, share an asset from a solution. 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult>
          <p>For example, see 
				<xref href="t_share_analytics_usecase.xml#task_F7AE118436FA4E01BFAF79B485482820" format="dita" scope="local"><?xm-replace_text Share an Analytics report to the Marketing Cloud?></xref>.
				
			 </p>
          <note>The Share button in solutions lets you create a card from the
				asset and share it to a Marketing Cloud board. You can also create a board when
				sharing an asset from within a solution. 
			 </note>
        </stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>